&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;mozTocH2&quot; name=&quot;mozTocId469715&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;The “Inverse Journey” of “Religious Morality” (from bad to worse)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &quot;religious morality&quot; of Judaism and Christianity also had flaws, as they allowed the taking of captive women as slaves. However, this concept of &quot;religious morality&quot; took an even worse turn with the arrival of Islam.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
