&lt;td&gt;The&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sachsenspiegel&quot; title=&quot;Sachsenspiegel&quot;&gt;Sachsenspiegel&lt;/a&gt;, the most influential German code of law from the&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_Ages&quot; title=&quot;Middle Ages&quot;&gt;Middle Ages&lt;/a&gt;, condemns slavery as a violation of man's likeness to God.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-19&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_abolition_of_slavery_and_serfdom#cite_note-19&quot;&gt;[19]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
