&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_X_of_France&quot; title=&quot;Louis X of France&quot;&gt;Louis X&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;publishes a decree abolishing&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavery&quot; title=&quot;Slavery&quot;&gt;slavery&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;and proclaiming that &quot;France signifies freedom&quot;, that any slave setting foot on French ground should be freed.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-21&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_abolition_of_slavery_and_serfdom#cite_note-21&quot;&gt;[21]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;However some limited cases of slavery continued until the 17th century in some of France's Mediterranean harbours in&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provence&quot; title=&quot;Provence&quot;&gt;Provence&lt;/a&gt;, as well as until the 18th century in some of&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overseas_France&quot; title=&quot;Overseas France&quot;&gt;France's overseas territories&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-EltisBradley2011_22-0&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_abolition_of_slavery_and_serfdom#cite_note-EltisBradley2011-22&quot;&gt;[22]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Most aspects of serfdom are also eliminated de facto between 1315 and 1318.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-encyclopedia1_23-0&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_abolition_of_slavery_and_serfdom#cite_note-encyclopedia1-23&quot;&gt;[23]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
