&lt;td&gt;Slavery abolished (including Sweden's territory in&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finland&quot; title=&quot;Finland&quot;&gt;Finland&lt;/a&gt;). However, slaves are not banned entry into the country until 1813.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-25&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeline_of_abolition_of_slavery_and_serfdom#cite_note-25&quot;&gt;[25]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Between 1784 and 1847, slavery was practiced in the Swedish-ruled Caribbean island of&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Barth%C3%A9lemy&quot; title=&quot;Saint Barthélemy&quot;&gt;Saint Barthélemy&lt;/a&gt;. Sweden never practiced serfdom, except in a few territories it later acquired which were ruled under a local legal code.&lt;/td&gt;
